<subSubSection id="4A7A811C5B501CCA68F4F57252D8F06D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="90CD1FA41D5C22423B0C933640CDBE54" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1FC31D7BB9633DE60630CDBC3A378CC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Chiapas, Oaxaca, Puebla, Veracruz), Guatemala (Baja Verapaz, Izabal, 
<normalizedToken id="9990C916848007A4D8A6DD374972A247" originalValue="Petén">Peten</normalizedToken>
), Belize, and Honduras, in primary or secondary high forest or tropical dry forest, very rarely in cloud forest at the upper part of its elevational range, often on limestone, 80-1000 (1500) m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="72FB3490978D6BACC44AD6FA7E9F9AE8" captionStart="Figure 85" captionStartId="F85" captionText="Figure 85. Map of geographic distribution of L. purpusii based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure85" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480099" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">85</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
